<span id="freeTextContainer14805390179385984441">I loved this book. The author first explains the conflict between science and religion and how scientists were prosecuted by religious entities. He speaks then about various topics that are very debatable like the soul, Sufism, free will, etc,, <br/><br/>He states that science need a lot to answer but he is always winning the battles against religion.. He also explains many philosophical ideas that science don&apos;t need to answer. <br/><br/>Interesting</span>
  <span id="freeText14805390179385984441" style="display:none">I loved this book. The author first explains the conflict between science and religion and how scientists were prosecuted by religious entities. He speaks then about various topics that are very debatable like the soul, Sufism, free will, etc,, <br /><br />He states that science need a lot to answer but he is always winning the battles against religion.. He also explains many philosophical ideas that science don't need to answer. <br /><br />Interesting</span>
