              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13239808617327379298">In spite of the title, the book provides readers more than just the conflict between science and religion. Bertrand Russell took us to explore soul, body, mysticism, logic, determinism and the relationship between science, ethic and education. Although I have read books regarding these issues before, this piece of writing refreshes what I&apos;ve known and filled me with new angle to approach the the problems.</span>
  <span id="freeText13239808617327379298" style="display:none">In spite of the title, the book provides readers more than just the conflict between science and religion. Bertrand Russell took us to explore soul, body, mysticism, logic, determinism and the relationship between science, ethic and education. Although I have read books regarding these issues before, this piece of writing refreshes what I've known and filled me with new angle to approach the the problems.</span>
