        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer24567643" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13310826643547716247">Not a lot to this one - I was surprised by how light on it was. There were some themes I really would have liked to have heard more on. He talks about Marxism (coming from Hegel) being based on Dialectics and this being somewhat similar to mysticism - <i>all is one, everything is related to everything else</i> - but does no more than mention this.<br/><br/>I would have liked more detail and more depth.<br/><br/>The thing I found most interesting about this was finding out that this book was written when Russell was in his</span>
  <span id="freeText13310826643547716247" style="display:none">Not a lot to this one - I was surprised by how light on it was. There were some themes I really would have liked to have heard more on. He talks about Marxism (coming from Hegel) being based on Dialectics and this being somewhat similar to mysticism - <i>all is one, everything is related to everything else</i> - but does no more than mention this.<br /><br />I would have liked more detail and more depth.<br /><br />The thing I found most interesting about this was finding out that this book was written when Russell was in his 60s and therefore forms something close to the mid-point of his career. Now, wouldn't that be a nice thing?</span>
  <a data-text-id="13310826643547716247" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

